      "content": "In low-cost areas with thin margins, the risk of going under due to increased costs is indeed a more pressing concern than the potential benefits of higher wages. The math often doesn't favor small businesses, and the likelihood of being pushed out of business by a wage hike is higher in these areas. This is why many small shop owners in rural areas are concerned that minimum wage hikes will disproportionately harm their businesses.",
